The United States and Vietnam have agreed to enhance their cooperation in the civil nuclear clean energy field. They aim to strengthen their commitment to nuclear safety, security, and nonproliferation. They have signed an Administrative Arrangement to facilitate the implementation of their agreement on nuclear energy. The two countries plan to establish a Joint Committee on Civil Nuclear Cooperation to promote cooperation and information sharing in various areas, including nuclear safety and security. They also aim to establish a Technical Support Center for Nuclear Security and Safeguards in Vietnam. Additionally, the United States will provide training and education opportunities in civil nuclear energy, safety, and security. They will also assist Vietnam in strengthening its nuclear regulatory capacity and export controls. Furthermore, the two countries will work together to secure nuclear and radiological materials and enhance incident response capabilities. Finally, they will promote joint training programs for Vietnamese officials in nuclear science and engineering and support bilateral civil nuclear trade.